727299f-b.title: Queens: Macnish Street - Elmhurst Avenue
727299f-b.text:
Naenish Street, east aide, between Elmhurst Avenue and
Forty-third Avenue, showing four views of the Saruel Lord
ansion from 1852 to 1873. Thoras warren was an occugant
in 1873. Weet of the mansion stood Daniel Bloormfield's house
in 1666. His house was razed by fire in 1872. All this proprrty
came into the possession of Samuel Lord in 1840. Dr. Coombs was
an occupant in 1924.
192
Viww 21 March 1924
V1rws 3\&4:May 1929
